title: Buttercup
lastfmSummary: With a strained, emotional vocal track filled with grooving and soothing guitar solos, this first track on Jack Stauber’s 2017 album Pop Food kicks things off with an engaging combination of synths and a kicking bass. While some of it may seem to be complete nonsense, with lines such as “electrify my golden tooth,” it isn’t. When asked in a New Retro interview how he writes his lyrics, Jack Stauber replied: I get playful with the words but they’re always chosen very carefully. Read more on Last.fm.
